 In the First World War, the Indian Army was 161,000 strong. More than half the soldiers were recruited from Punjab. The Indian Corps won 13,000 medals for gallantry, including 12 Victoria Crosses in World War 1.

 India gate was built in memory of the 82 thousand soldiers who were martyred in World War One.

 The Indian Military Training Team (IMTRAT) is permanently stationed in western Bhutan.

